cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.OH, cs.PL 

The paper focuses on the role of university staff in developing research software and analyzing different models of organization and their consequences on the staff and software. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and also involves aspects of cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY), computer engineering (cs.CE), open science (cs.OH), and programming languages (cs.PL).
